    "summary": "Buddhism expert importance weights for translator profile",
    "content": "1: 10 -- Non-negotiable. Mistranslating the source undermines everything.\n2: 9 -- The essays ARE philosophy. A literary-only translator will flatten the arguments.\n3: 8 -- The cat essay, the dreamscape metaphor, the \"poetry of raising a cat\" passages require literary instinct.\n4: 7 -- Needed for the two category theory essays. Can be supplemented by the category theory expert consultant, but the translator must at minimum be able to typeset and not mangle the notation.\n5: 9 -- The author shifts between colloquial storytelling (the cat), classical Chinese allusion (道德仁义礼), formal definition, and mathematical notation, sometimes within a single essay. This is perhaps the hardest skill to find.\n6: 8 -- The 道德仁义礼 passage is central to the post-metaphysics essay. The translator must know the existing English conventions to either follow or consciously depart from them.\n7: 9 -- As we established, the essays are philosophical experiments. Disrupting sequence = breaking the experiment.\n8: 7 -- Needed for accurate rendering of the author's engagement with Camus (absurdity), Heidegger (Dasein-adjacent concepts), and the phenomenological vocabulary. The experts can consult, but the translator should recognize standard renderings.\n9: 6 -- Important for 境, 境界, 虚無 vs. 空, 清醒/覺, and other terms with Buddhist semantic layers. However, this is precisely what I am here to consult on. A translator who can read my term dictionary intelligently and flag questions is sufficient; they do not need to be a Buddhologist.\n10: 6 -- The author engages Kantian structures (phenomena, thing-in-itself parallels, a priori structures) but does not use Kantian terminology directly. The Kantian expert can consult. The translator needs enough familiarity to render the parallels accurately when flagged.\n11: 4 -- Lowest priority. The author does not engage analytic philosophy of language directly. The Wittgenstein references are identifiable and the expert can consult. The translator does not need this register natively.\n"
  }
